    "summary": "The user presents symptoms of a potential ankle fracture (swelling, inability to bear weight, and a crooked appearance) and asks about self-treating at home. The assistant initially encourages the RICE method and suggests the user will be fine, but then correctly pivots to recommending an X-ray when the user mentions the deformity. Finally, the assistant correctly advises against high doses of medication and suggests acetaminophen instead.",
